CreditData(11)=(LineType=CreditsLineDefinition'UI_Credits.LineStyles.Title',Text="Personal Thanks")
CreditData(12)=(LineType=CreditsLineDefinition'UI_Credits.LineStyles.Body',Text="To Michelle and Noel:  Your support and understanding during the long hours kept me going.  You are the best.\n    Love, Paul Hellquist\n\nSpecial thanks to my wife Sobia, for her support while working on Borderlands 2.\n  - Awais Ahmed\n\nThank you for everything Weiwei.  Wo ai ni.\n  - Daniel Algood\n\nThanks to Lori, and all my friends and family for all their love and support.\n  - Parker Amos\n\nThanks to my wife and daughter for their wonderful smiles and support!\n  - Robert Anderson\n\nThanks to Emily, Alexander (creator of the Norfleet) and Evelyn.  Hey, Boo.\n  - Matthew Armstrong\n\n"I cut the line!" Miss you dude. Keep doing your best every day Wildcard Dougy.\n  - Joshua Ball\n\nTo my beautiful wife Brandy, thank you for love and support.\n  - Ray Barham\n\nJeff, Stephen, Andrew, Alex, Chris, Dustin, KP, Jon, Stephanie, Kevin, Mishell, Crystin, Ben, Rachel, Jacob, Nic, Ellen, Dan, Ken, Kate, Jessica, Robin, Kelly, Apryl, and Shelby. Your name is in a game now!  Also to my Mom and Dad. Thank you guys for letting me grow up to be a kid.\n  - James Barnett\n\nThanks to my Family, Friends and Coworkers. Thanks to all of our playtesters too.\n  - Kyle Beasley\n\nThanks to my friends and family for supporting me all these years.\n  - Uriah Belletto\n\nThanks to everyone who helped me get to where I am, especially my parents Brenda and Dalton.\n  - Dalton Boutte\n\nThanks to HBD, Blavis, Ash, Linde, my family, Niero, Mikey, and not Keith Schuler. And Anthony Clark, for the word "bonerfart."\n  - Anthony Burch\n\nThank you Kristen for all the love and support that you give me every day ... and HEY MOM, I'M ON TV!\n  - Paul Burt\n\nMy work would not be possible if it were not for my beautiful wife Christina who supported me every step of the way.\n  - Ruben Cabrera\n\nTo my girls, Erica, Vanna & Rio, thank you for supporting the leap...SFSA.\n  - Wade Callender\n\nThank you for your love and support Rachael and Emily.\n  - Mike Carlyle\n\nSpecial thanks to Ray's mom.\n  - James Cart\n\nThanks to NB, the lizard, and Slappy\n  - Jennifer Chung\n\nFor Natasha and Kieran\n  - Stephen Cole\n\nMany loves to Maya and Jamie!\n  - Jeramy Cooke\n\nThanks to my family and my fiancé for their love and support. I couldn't have done this without them.\n  - Leigh-Ann Cox\n\nMy awesome family and friends. A very special thanks to you, Boo! And to Everyone at Gearbox.\n  - Kandis Daniel\n\nI'd like to thank my mom and step-dad for their encouragement and support as well as my friends Aaron, Chris, Jason, Jed, and Chris H.  Plus a special thank you to all my awesome coworkers at Gearbox who sacrificed many hours of their life to craft this wonderful game for everyone to enjoy.\n  - Peter Dannenberg\n\nMy heartfelt thanks to my supportive family and treasured friends, the CMU ETC, Dr. Richard Lamberski, Dr. Jesse Schell, Ralph Vituccio and to my 2nd family, Gearbox! Thanks for taking a chance on me, four and a half years ago, to be a part of this amazing and talented team!\n  - Trey Davenport\n\nThank you to my parents, and to my brother Chuck for their constant support.\n  - Justin DeLiberis\n\nTo Richard De Vore, I love you as much as you love me + 1\n  - Jasmine De Vore\n\nThanks to my parents for being awesome and helping me over the past few years in pursuing this awesome career. Happy (almost) birthday, Dad!\n  - Jeff Doering\n\nThank you Sarah, Charlie, Mom, Davey, Chip, Carey, Bubba, Nana - Love you all\n  - Ben Donges\n\nThanks to Amanda for sticking through it and always supporting me.  Love ya babes.\n  - Kevin Duc\n\nThanks to my beautiful wife, my supportive family, our fervent fans, and robots...especially robots.\n  - James "the CMO" Dwyer\n\nDedicated to my family for always believing, and to Pamela for her unreserved love and support.\n  - Fredric Echols\n\nThanks to my wife, Tahmmy Eddings, for keeping me grounded; and my sons, Alex Eddings and Aidan Eddings, for keeping me young.\n  - David Eddings\n\nStephanie, I cannot express deeply enough my thanks for all your support, understanding and--most importantly--the love and joy you bring me.  "Oluvya, olways hav."\n  - Don Eubanks\n\nFor Ame, Bridget, Robert, Michael, and all my friends from LeviStad. Sieg UNOC!\n  - Steven Fast\n\nTo all those that have filled my life with the inspiration, support and encouragement to pursue my dreams -- I hope you find what you're looking for. Also, dinosaurs. \n  - Chris Faylor\n\nSomething clever? Something thoughtful? Nah . . . Balungas!\n  - Patrick Fenn\n\nThanks to my wonderful wife Kathryn for letting me abandon "Corporate America" hell, and to our boys Miles and Mason!\n  - David Fisk\n\nWords can't express the gratitude I have for the seemingly endless patience and understanding displayed by my fiancée Angela Adams. By the time you read this, you'll be stuck with my last name! I also want to thank the supremely talented Artists that worked on this project. Hopefully I managed to make your lives easier in some little way. Now get back to work!\n  - Rich Fleider\n\nThanks to my amazing Mom, Dad and Brother for always sticking with my goals/aspirations in life.  Thanks to my friends, especially my best friend Richard for being so awesome.  Thanks to my dog Toby for not peeing/pooping everywhere when I worked long hours or was always traveling due to press tours! And thanks to everyone at Gearbox for being the most talented group of people in the business and having an awesome Marketing/PR team that I call my second home... I love working with you all!\n  - Adam Fletcher\n\nThanks to my wife Meredith and our friends and family. To our fans who make this possible. Borderlands 2 was a great ride. Enjoy the experience Vault Hunters!\n  - Zach Ford\n\nMy badass wife, Lindy and my badass sons, Draven and Tavin.\n  - Mark Forsyth\n\nThank you to all my friends near and far for putting up with me all these years, my family; parents James and Sheryl and brother Mike for putting up with me my entire life, and to my adorable Fluttershy.\n  - Chris Francis\n\nThanks to William Jeremy Counseller, the best professor at Baylor Law School. Thumbs-up on jurisdiction.\n  - Brian Fuller\n\nShout out to my family and to James Webb (who passed out).  Ya we pumpin'!\n  - Ben Gettleman\n\nThe winding path of internet, ramen, pizza and blogs. I still can't figure out how the rest of this all happened. I would like to thank my wife Aimee for being on board this roller coaster of mixed metaphors though. Choo Choo!\n  - Steve Gibson\n\nMom, Dad, Grandmas and Grandpas, Joe, Katrina, Carol, Brandon, Cherry, Adam W., Phil W., and all  my friends and family, love you guys.\n  - Evan Gill\n\nMy family for their love and support, especially my wife Bonnie for bringing me dinner on those long work nights!\n  - Jeff Giron\n\nThanks to my amazing wife Nienke. Shout out to Thiago, and the folks at Shacknews.\n  - Maarten Goldstein\n\nThank you to my wonderful wife Kristy Hadley aka "Sugar" for putting up with the kids while I was busy making history.\n    Love, Dia Hadley :)\n\nThanks to everybody from the K-Board for being so awesome!\n  - Shaylyn Hamm\n\nTo Ella Bear, my best friend, thanks for being there when no one else was\n  - Ryan Heaton\n\nThanks Phoebe and nameless unborn child.\n  - Jonathan Hemingway\n\nSpecial thanks to the 3 most supportive people in my life....my parents and my bro.\n  - Andrew Hoffman\n\nThanks to my husband Will, sisters Lynsay and Maggie, brothers Conner, Lukas, and Nick, and the rest of my loving family and friends for their support!\n  - James Houchen\n\nFor Jeff, for putting up with all the long hours.  You may never be able to walk and chew gum at the same time, but I love you anyway.   :)\n  - Josh Jeffcoat\n\nTricia Skinner, Myque Ouellette, Michael McCoy, thanks for getting me started and shoving me in the right direction. Sky and G. Henry, thanks for staying up super late every night with me making stuff cool. Shaylyn, thanks for liking game fanart and everything else. To all of my tremendous GBX colleagues, thanks for taking a chance on me and believing in me. You know who you are! Hi Mom, Brandan, Angel, dziadzia, babcia!\n  - Skyler Jermyn\n\nThanks to all of QA, Past & Present. To Marc; To Kath; To Rob: <3\n  - Kirsten Kahler\n\nThanks to God, Raegan, and Nova...my power. For anyone who ever believed in any of my fool's crusades, I never forget.\n  - Scott Kester\n\nMost awesomeness persons ever - Sandeep, Nathan, Kallan, Daniel, Little J, Pradeep, Alix, & Mathieu\n  - Kyle King\n\nI am grateful for actually having time to be able to write this note. And also to my wife and son for letting me work here and not be mad that I get to help make great games all day.\n  - Jesse Kirstein\n\nPersonal thanks to: The Monkey\n  - James Lee\n\nTo my parents, Mark and Donna; my sister, Amanda; and the Lightfoot and Bukowski Clans: Thank you all for your love and support.\n  - Justin Lightfoot\n\nThank you my wonderful husband Andrew Lindwall for letting me follow my dream. Le grá go deo.\n  - Lilith Lindwall\n\nTo my wife Kristen, for her never-ending patience and support. I love you!\n  - James Lopez\n\nThanks to my wife Karen and my life obstacles Sean, Riley, and Rachel.\n  - Jeff Macfee\n\nThank you to the Martel family for being a behinds the scenes glue for Gearbox and all of our games. Your strength makes all of this possible and is truly appreciated.\n  - Brian Martel\n\nHeartfelt thanks to my family and friends, and to my angel, Melissa.\n  - Curry McKnight\n\nI'd like to say thanks to my family, Dad, Mom, Tickie, Aaron, Melissa, Matt, Jennifer. Thanks to my friends for their support, and to my coworkers who inspire me with their talents. Thanks to Martha for letting me get away from it all.\n  - Drew Mobley\n\nSabrina, I can't thank you enough for the incredible support you've given me.\n  - Aaron Nations\n\nThank you Dad for giving me all the tools, opportunities, and support to do what I love. Thank you for always being proud! I Love you and miss you!\n  - Jason Neal\n\nI'd like to thank my family and especially my brother Nick. I miss you all.\n  - Chris Neeley\n\nA heartfelt thank you to all of the friends and family that were there for me while I was in the hospital. A bigger thank you to the people that brought me Korean tacos, because, um, hello? Yum!\n  - Mike Neumann\n\nThanks Mom & Dad, Tuan & Hmong, Mary & Charlie, Lucy & Phong for your support. A big shout out to BigLong, Chicken, DuaneCThomas, JMart, JWise, Longstick,  SDam, Skubee Raw, and TuanJohn. Last but not least, my rugrat nieces and nephews; Maddie, Noah, Sophie, Simon, and Sawyer.\n  - Tu Nguyen\n\nWoohoo! First game! Thanks, Mike & Jackie for sending me to Art school and P.S. Amy, you smell. :D\n  - Ricky Oh\n\nThanks to my family, friends and my amazing wife Jackie!\n  - Josh Olson\n\nThank you Avie for being all giggles and smiles when I get home after a long day. You are the reason I do this. I love you.\n  - Nathan Overman\n\nKim, Mom, and Dad; thank you for your support. I love you!\n  - Gilberto Perez\n\nMy family rocks.  :-D\n  - Ben Perkins\n\nLoyce Pickett, Aisley Pickett, Cleo Pickett, and the rest of the Pickett family for their consistent love, support, and patience. I wouldn't be here without you all.\n  - Chris Pickett\n\nEndless thanks to my muse Kristy Junio Pitchford and our son, Randall S. Pitchford III.\n  - Randy Pitchford\n\nThanks to David and Kim and Thomas (who will totally be a real boy by the time you're reading this), Mom and Dad, Sammy (the cutest cuddliest little kitten ever), Lara (also a cat), Smash Crew, themillnet, the Guildhall, unnecessary parentheses, fourth walls, and you! Ship it!\n  - J. Kyle Pittman\n\nTo the friends and lovers who supported me and broke my heart.  You all make life worth living.\n  - Rick Porter\n\nTo my friends and family: Thank you for all the love and support while working on BL2. I couldn't have done it without you.\n  - Stephanie Puri\n\nLeah Reiss, for all the love and support. Oh and putting up with me.\n  - Jason Reiss\n\nFor my brilliant husband Curtis, our little monsters Athos and Pogo, and my friends, Travis, Stacy, Matt A, Matt O, Ben, James, Parker, and Mike Dawson.\n  - Ashley Rochelle\n\nThanks to my wife and my son for their continued patience, and for allowing me the chance to follow this crazy dream.\n  - Kelly Romeo\n\nThanks to my family Annie & Carter for being so great!\n  - Tim Roth\n\nI would like to thank Robert Santiago "Environment Artist".\n  - Robert Santiago\n\nBack to back against the world, my love! Keep being tolerant and telling the kids Daddy's weird.\n  - Keith Schuler\n\nSpecial thanks to all the super talented Gearbox employees that worked so hard on Borderlands 2. You make this awesome!\n  - Chase Sensky\n\nHello? Thank you Emily for your love, support, patience, and for being my best friend. I love you very much. Are we cool? Definitely. Is that cool? Yes. MANGAS!\n  - Eric Shaddix\n\nI would like to thank my amazing, lovely, supportive wife, Jenni, and my handsome boys Connor and Collin!  You guys inspire me each and every day.  I love you!  And finally, my broseph kin: Kyle J, Adam M, Alex Y, Nathan and Ian J, Jonathan H, and Phil C.\n  - Carl Shedd\n\nJulie, Mom, Dad, Todd, Dennis  thanks for everything, I love you guys!\n  - Jason Shields\n\nThanks to my wife Lisa for all her support and love. Thanks to my mom and dad for encouraging me to pursue my dreams.\n  - Jimmy Sieben\n\nThank you, Sarah, for your patience and understanding. You're such a wonderful wife and mother! Burt and Daniel, thanks for your patience too  Enjoy!  Dan, now that you have a console, no more excuses!\n  - Leo Sieben\n\nFinally! These long nights are finally paying off. Thanks to all my family and friends who supported me along the way.\n  - Brad Sierzega\n\nTo Strobel, thank you for putting your life into this game  it is better for it because of you. To QA, thanks for all of the hard work and late hours  you guys rocked it out! \n  - Gabriel Simon\n\nThanks to my mom, grandmother, and brother for molding me into the man I am today. Thanks to all of Team Awesome for their support, especially my best friends throughout the years: Wes P., Jacquie U., Kevin W., Jeff. M, Kyle B., Steve P., Michael G., Eric L., and Andrew R.\n  - Steven Strobel\n\nThanks to Richard Howdy, Josh Lam, Ashleigh Miller, Meagan Leonard, Matthew Horton, Rachel Johnson, Sara Wedell and Paul and Paulette Timmins.\n  - Graeme Timmins\n\nThank you Gearbox family for making games like BL2 that we're proud of and love to play.  2K you're always great partners.  Thanks to the games industry, you've all been amazingly supportive.  Super special thanks to Myrna, Jonah and Ariel, my favorite co-op buddies and personal coaches.\n  - Aaron Thibault\n\nThank you to my wonderful partner Liz for being my muse and to my family and friends for all of the love and support I could wish for.\n  - Brian Thomas\n\nThanks to God for the chance to work on my dreams; thanks to my parents for feeding my dreams; thanks to my wife Carrie and my kids Rachel and Graham for being more than I dreamed.\n  - Randy Varnell\n\nThanks to my family for giving me a reason to come home and relax, you guys keep life refreshing and fun.  Shout out to Ez and Kendra, keep your heads up!\n  - Scott Velasquez\n\nBest ever developing experience, Thanks team!\n  - Taku Wanifuchi\n\nThank you to my wonderful husband, Chancey, and my family (blood or other) for all your support and encouragement when the days/nights get long. Congratulations, Gearbox family - YOU ROCK AND SO DOES THIS GAME!!!\n  - Hayley Williamson\n\nThank you Shovaen, for all your patience and support.\n  - Lori Wilson\n\nI'd like to thank my family and Gearbox. Borderlands 2 is here, September 18 20XX, I wish I could see each fan break the seal on their new game.\n  - Nicholas Wilson\n\nMichael "Archangel" Castro\n  - Al Wood\n\nThanks to my wife Jessica, and my daughter Hanna for being very understanding during this project. Also thanks to my parents, Kelley and Sheryl, and all my friends and family.\n  - Hunter Wright\n\nI would like to thank my family for their support and Boris Batkin for answering many technical questions for me.\n  - David Ziman\n\n\nMom, Dad, thank you for your unending love and support. To my family and friends, this has been a surreal ride and I can't ever repay you for the strength and encouragement you've given me to help make this possible. I wouldn't be here without you.\n\nAnd to those who have made it this far, thank you for sticking around - I hope you're enjoying Borderlands 2!\n  - Matt Charles\n\n\n")
